Nigeria on Saturday recorded six hundred and sixty-one, 661, new COVID-19 cases in the country. The Nigeria Centre for Disease Control, NCDC, confirmed the development in a tweet on Saturday night. The data released indicated that Lagos had 230 cases while Rivers followed with 127. With this development, Nigeria now has a total of 19,808 confirmed cases of the infection and 506 deaths. NCDC tweeted, “661 new cases of COVID-19 in Nigeria; Lagos-230 Rivers-127 Delta-83 FCT-60 Oyo-51 Edo-31 Bayelsa-27 Kaduna-25 Plateau-13 Ondo-6 Nasarawa-3 Ekiti-2 Kano-2 Borno-1 “19,808 confirmed. 6,718 discharged. “506 deaths.”